body:
@joelrich in your case, you should probably use a TimeDistributed layer to make inference for more than one step ahead. Assuming you're predicting sequences.

https://keras.io/layers/wrappers/

If you're just predicting independent variables, then a Dense(nb_classes) without a softmax would also work I guess.

@philipperemy I didn't even need to create a new example. I just took the copy_memory example and changed classes=0 and regression=True -- this is a regression problem that has many input time steps and many output time steps.

So I think this is just a nomenclature issue. Per https://machinelearningmastery.com/encoder-decoder-long-short-term-memory-networks/

> Given that there are multiple input time steps and multiple output time steps, this form of problem is referred to as many-to-many type sequence prediction problem.
